<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-08-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-08-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="626" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d626">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Rockhill</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Lee</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi></placeName>,<lb/><date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-08-18"><hi rend="italic">August
                                        18, 1896</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Newspaper advices from Key West of 16th state that Charles Govin, an
                            American citizen and correspondent, was captured near Jaruco by Spanish
                            troops and put to death. Investigate and report by cable.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Rockhill</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Acting.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>